D‑Scope is an open, modular protocol designed to unify environmental, flow,
energy and HVAC monitoring across heterogeneous hardware platforms. It includes:

• A machine‑readable Registry defining all protocol fields and modules
• A formal DPCR (D‑Scope Protocol Change Request) process governing protocol evolution
• A set of firmware modules targeting ESP32, RP2040, PIC and other MCUs
• Shared libraries implementing the D‑Scope protocol and utilities
• Tools for validation, conversion, analysis and documentation generation

This distribution may include contributions from external authors. All
contributions are governed by the Apache License 2.0 unless otherwise stated.

The D‑Scope Registry (fields.json and modules.json) is the authoritative source
of truth for all protocol definitions. Any modification to the Registry must be
proposed through a DPCR and validated before inclusion.

The D‑Scope protocol, Registry, and associated tools are intended to remain
fully open and interoperable. Implementations may be proprietary or open‑source,
provided that this NOTICE file and the Apache License 2.0 are preserved in any
redistribution.

